<br>
2 P'tasa kills in maybe 6 trips to Hate.<br>
1 trip to PoA 7.<br>
Maybe 4 Phinny kills<br>
1 Undertow.<br>
<br>
I honestly believe that people exaggerate the number of times they've killed certain mobs and not gotten drops.  <br>
<br>
I can believe that Phinny or Hate can take a good number of kills, although I don't believe that anyone has actually killed P'tasa 49 times and not gotten a staff.  If you limit your Hate raids to the weekends, then I can see how you may never find P'tasa up, though.<br>
<br>
I also flat don't believe that someone has killed Undertow 25 times and not gotten a drop.  In my experience, he drops the wand 60-70% of the time.  Even assuming it's more like 50%, the odds of killing him 25 times and no drop are 0.00000298%<br>
<br>
I understand probabilities and statistics and the fact that it is theoretically possible for someone to kill any of these mobs forever and not see a drop.  The number of people posting outrageous numbers of kills without seeing a drop is simply not believable.  They're made up just to get a little comiseration.<br>
<br>
